com.logimethods.connector.spark.to_nats

Class SparkToNatsConnector<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.logimethods.connector.spark.to_nats.SparkToNatsConnector<T>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable

    public abstract class SparkToNatsConnector<T>
extends Object
    A Spark to NATS connector.

    That connector provides way to send to NATS all the records belonging to a Spark RDD, such as follow: 

    rdd.foreach(
    SparkToNatsConnector
        .newConnection()
        .withNatsURL(NATS_SERVER_URL)
        .withSubjects("subject1", "subject2")
        .withConnectionTimeout(Duration.ofSeconds(1))
        .publishToNats());
    Author:
    Laurent Magnin
    See Also:
    (Java based) NATS / Spark Connectors, Serialized Form

      • publishToNatsAsKeyValue

        public <K,V> void publishToNatsAsKeyValue(org.apache.spark.api.java.JavaRDD<scala.Tuple2<K,V>> rdd)
        A method that will publish all the records of the provided Spark RDD, made of Key/Value Tuples, into NATS. The subjects of the NATS messages will be a combination of the global NATS Subjects with the individual Keys, while the NATS message payloads will the the individual Tuples' values.
        Parameters:
        rdd, - the RDD to publish to NATS

      • publishToNatsAsKeyValue

                                          Function<V,byte[]> dataEncoder)
        A method that will publish all the records of the provided Spark RDD, made of Key/Value Tuples, into NATS. The subjects of the NATS messages will be a combination of the global NATS Subjects with the individual Keys, while the NATS message payloads will the the individual Tuples' values.
        Parameters:
        rdd, - the RDD to publish to NATS
        dataEncoder, - the function used to encode the records of the RDD to populate the payload of the NATS Messages
